description: Up for sale now in our Houston Showroom is this 1965 Ford Mustang.   With Ã¢??65 being the first official year of the Mustang, some early build cars were called Ã¢??64.5Ã¢?Â cars, and had unique options. One of those unique options is the 289 CID V8 engine perfectly set under the long, sporty hood. Backing that with a 4-speed manual transmission makes for a great driving experience anywhere you go. This Stang is painted in Bright Cherry red that shows very well.  The car was professionally repainted about a year ago during its frame off restoration and it shows they did a very nice job.  The body panels align like they should with minimal gap variation.   All of the exterior body trim, emblems, & window trim is in great condition.  The 289 CID V8 went through a very recent rebuild by D&A General Auto here in Houston, TX roughly less than 500 miles ago.  During that rebuild the engine was bored .30 over & had a race camshaft installed to give it that muscle car loping sound we all love.  The engine also features a new high flow Weiand carburetor, electronic ignition, & long tube race headers.  Looking towards the interior you will find several fairly new items such as the vinyl seats, new carpet, door panels, & a cool que ball shifter.  The dash is also in excellent condition showing the gauge cluster & glove box in like new condition.  The car has new 15 inch wheels that are wrapped in new Barum tires.   The car also features disc brakes in the front, new front & rear struts with air shocks in the rear.  The undercarriage of the car looks great as well, showing hardly any traces of rust with new bushings in all the right places & components.  This a great car at a great price that anyone from a high school graduate to a new retired executive could enjoy for years to come.  The car features new door speakers that are powered by a CD player with AM/FM radio. Absolutely Phenomenal 1965 Ford Mustang Fastback Coupe

The next amazing vehicle up for grabs in our Benicia showroom is this 1965 Ford Mustang Fastback Coupe with red exterior paint and a black vinyl interior.  You’ll find a freshly rebuilt 289 cid V-8 engine under the hood with a Holly 600 4bbl carburetor and a C4 automatic transmission, and this lifetime California classic is sensational from bumper to bumper.  With only 8,891 miles on the odometer, you simply will not find a more breathtaking example anywhere on the West Coast within this price range.
Drivetrain Restored to Outstanding Level

The current owner of this 1965 Ford Mustang Fastback Coupe is the third to enjoy it and he purchased this classic back in 2015.  Since that time, he has replaced the front and rear bumpers, the dashboard, the door panels, the tie end rods, the control arms, the ball joints, the wheels/tires, the complete sound system and speakers, and so much more.  The factory engine was also pulled and bored .040 over and the C4 transmission was completely rebuilt with a new torque converter.  The current owner also added GT fog lights (not hooked up), a GT emblem kit, a GT gas cap and the Rally Pack (not hooked up).  This was a very high end classic muscle car before the restoration effort and now it borders on perfection.

In terms of physical condition, this 1965 Ford Mustang Fastback has show-quality exterior paint across the body- there may be a minor blemish somewhere but we’ve yet to see it.  The interior is also like-new in appearance with the only wear to be found residing on the floor mats- everything else is exceptional.  There is simply nothing here not to like on this prestigious example and the performance is truly world-class- it gets down the road in a hurry with an unbelievable feel.
An Incredible Classic Performance Machine that’s Ready to Enjoy

Overall, this 1965 Ford Mustang Fastback is one of the most outstanding examples that we’ve seen in quite some time and it may drive “better than new” after an extensive restoration effort.  It would be a pinnacle in any serious collection and you absolutely must see it in person to understand the level of quality.  This one won’t last long.  For more information about this impressive vehicle, visit our Benicia, California showroom, give us a call at

description: As Lee Iacocca's assistant general manager and chief engineer, Donald N. Frey was the head engineer for the Mustang project - supervising the development of the Mustang in a record 18 months from September 1962 to March 1964 - while Iacocca himself championed the project as Ford Division general manager. One of the design requirements established by Ford for this Mustang was that it should be a 4-passenger car and this has been neatly accomplished while still retaining much of the ''coupe'' look. The 1966 Mustang debuted with moderate trim changes including a new grille, side ornamentation, wheel covers and gas cap. Ford's new C-4 ''cruise-o-matic'' three-speed auto transmission also became available for the 225 hp V8. This '66 Mustang Hardtop has lots of appeal, from it long, low lines to its recognizable engine growl it's what made this ''America's Favorite Fun Car''. There is plenty of room for the driver to get into the Mustang, the door being well placed in this respect, the bucket seats are above average and the shift lever is within comfortable reach. We're offering this 1966 Ford Mustang Hardtop adorned in RED over BLACK VINYL. This classic comes with $472 (in 1966) dollars in Extra Charge options including the CRUISE-O-MATIC 3-SPEED AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION, 289CID-2V 200HP V-8 ENGINE, POWER STEERING, RADIO & ANTENNA, TINTED GLASS WINDSHIELD, 2-SPEED ELECTRIC WINDSHIELD WIPERS & DAY/NIGHT REARVIEW MIRROR. Plus these aftermarket add-ons/upgrades DUAL EXHAUST, DISC BRAKES, CHROME AIR FILTER, CHROME VALVE COVERS, CHROME VALVE COVER BREATHER, CHROME OIL DIPSTICK, ALUMINUM RADIATOR, 14 INCH WHEELS, ''PREMIER'' REAR SPEAKERS, RED EXTERIOR PAINT. This vehicle also includes 1 set of keys and rubber floor mats. Comes comprehensively serviced and detailed by our highly regarded Bosch Authorized Service Facility. Trades Welcome.
